  "text": "ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable is defined in etcd-io/etcd/raft/storage.go (line 38) as a variable error: 'var ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable = errors.New(\"snapshot is temporarily unavailable\")'. This error is part of the Storage interface contract (also defined in storage.go) which specifies that the Snapshot() method can return this error when the required snapshot is temporarily unavailable.\n\nThe snapshot availability check during Raft log catch-up is implemented through a call chain:\n\n1. In etcd-io/etcd/raft/raft.go, the sendSnapshot() method (line 672-676) calls r.raftLog.snapshot() to retrieve a snapshot needed for a lagging follower. It explicitly checks if the returned error is ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable and gracefully returns false without panicking, allowing the leader to retry later.\n\n2. In etcd-io/etcd/raft/log.go, the snapshot() method (line 291-296) implements the actual snapshot retrieval by first checking for an unstable snapshot, then delegating to l.storage.Snapshot() which is provided by the Storage interface implementation.\n\n3. When a node (follower/learner) falls far behind during rejoin, the leader's sendSnapshot method is called. If the storage layer returns ErrSnapshotTemporarilyUnavailable, the raft layer handles this gracefully by not sending the snapshot immediately and allowing the storage layer time to prepare it, preventing the node rejoin from failing completely."
}

